text: Had Babat & Mutton Satay + Ketupat (~$20) for dinner on 2/7/24, was good! My personal favourite stall.

Ordered satay of 10s babat, 10s mutton & 10s chicken with 2 ketupat for $29. Lovely & friendly people. It was raining but they managed to got us a place outside beneath the big umbrella. Later on we got a quick change to the pondok when it was empty ! Thank you for the vibrant & welcoming gesture with great service. Always my favourite stall every time !

The Satay shop remains the solitary choice available on Sunday afternoons. The devoted staff goes above and beyond to entice customers with their warm and welcoming approach, even seeking feedback on their satay. The chicken satay offers a delightful, well-balanced flavor without overwhelming spiciness. Furthermore, their goreng dishes provide an equally satisfying culinary experience.
Haron’s satay wasn’t opened today so I tried satays from both stalls 59 and 60. Stall 59’s satay was more tender, juicier and the sauce also was better.
